  "contentHtml": "<p>1. <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.08525\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Do chatbots ever follow the interests of advertisers?</a></p>\n<p>2. <a href=\"https://x.com/gdb/status/2053134883040514350?s=46&amp;t=fSypFxt84bBHId-do9r5Ag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Approaching the Star Trek universal translator</a>.</p>\n<p>3. <a href=\"https://x.com/jonhaidt/status/2052469035221361094?s=46&amp;t=fSypFxt84bBHId-do9r5Ag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jon Haidt response to the new cell phone study</a>.</p>\n<p>4. <a href=\"https://x.com/tylercowen/status/2053135643656466833\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">U.S. electricity prices have been flat since June</a>.</p>\n<p>5. <a href=\"https://allakeselman.substack.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Friend Alla Keselman now has a Substack</a>.</p>\n<p>6. I am enjoying the new Elizabeth Strout novel <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Things-We-Never-Say-Novel-ebook/dp/B0FSQ3W7BC/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;pd_rd_w=qUEvw&amp;content-id=amzn1.sym.3a079c4e-f938-40c9-a0ed-01ef0e9528e9&amp;pf_rd_p=3a079c4e-f938-40c9-a0ed-01ef0e9528e9&amp;pf_rd_r=139-7026227-2249935&amp;pd_rd_wg=0x4mN&amp;pd_rd_r=34e858d5-4fb8-403a-8b25-ae628b7eff1b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Things We Never Say</a>.&nbsp; It is arguably “too American” for me, and also “too New England,” still it is quite good.</p>",
